      • computeSuccessors

        public Set<ProgramState> computeSuccessors(ProgramState programState,
                                           SymbolicExecutionObserver observer)
                                    throws NotSufficientlyMaterializedException,
                                           StateSpaceGenerationAbortedException
        gets the fixpoint from the AbstractMethod for the input heap and returns it for the successor location.

        If any variable appearing in the arguments is not live at this point, it will be removed from the heap to enable abstraction.

        Specified by:
        computeSuccessors in interface Semantics
        Parameters:
        programState - The state on which the abstract program semantics shall be executed.
        observer - A collection of configuration parameters to influence to symbolic execution.
        Returns:
        The set of all states resulting from executing the program semantics on programState.
        Throws:
        NotSufficientlyMaterializedException - This exception is thrown if the semantics cannot be executed on programState due to missing fields.
        StateSpaceGenerationAbortedException
